studyID: The stable, unique identifier for a study that never changes, even if other study metadata changes (like the study name, short name, owner, or project). Example: STUDY_SCA
optional persistent row identifier: Use studyID as the anchor, plus a persistent row identifier to identify a specific file/version, etc.
optional persistent row identifier - va: Enter a unique identifier for the selection made.
optional appliesTo: Indicates the level of entity to which a metadata value applies (e.g., individual participant or population summary).
optional aggregationLevel: Specifies whether a metadata value represents individual-level data or an aggregate summary
optional populationScope: Identifies the population described by the metadata (e.g., study-wide, cohort, or study arm).
derivedVariableName: The name of a derived variable or score as it appears in the dataset or metadata record.
derivedVariableType: A controlled category describing the general method or type of derivation used to compute a derived variable or score (e.g., sum score, composite score, standardized score).
variableSummary: Aggregate summary statistics describing the observed distribution and availability of a variable in a dataset, without exposing participant-level values.
scoreName: Is the human-readable name of a score derived from a measure, as used or labeled by the study.
scoreType: Describes the general method or form by which a score was derived from a measure or assessment.
derivedScore: A summary description of a score derived from a measure, including how it was calculated.
derivationMethod: A high-level description of how a score was derived from raw or intermediate data.
valueRange: The observed minimum and maximum values of a continuous variable within the reported population scope.
totalParticipants: The total number of unique participants for whom data are available within the specified study, cohort, or scope.
propotion: A numeric value representing the fraction of a population associated with a given category, typically expressed as a percentage or decimal.
dataAvailabilitySummary: An aggregate description of the amount and demographic composition of available data for a study, cohort, or variable, provided without individual-level records.
valueRangeMinValue: The minimum observed value of a continuous variable within the specified population scope.
valueRangeMaxValue: The maximum observed value of a continuous variable within the specified population scope.
unit: The unit of measurement associated with a variable’s values or summary statistics (e.g., years, kg/m²).
timepoint: A label identifying the study timepoint or phase at which the variable value or summary applies (e.g., baseline, follow-up).
